OL,3,CSouth of Scotland celebrates
OL,4,Clinguistic heritage during World
OL,5,CGaelic Week
OL,7,FA number of events have been held in
OL,8,Fthe south of Scotland to mark World
OL,9,FGaelic Week, as the region celebrates
OL,10,Fit's linguistic heritage.
OL,12,FThey have included talks on Gaelic
OL,13,Fculture and history for adults, music
OL,14,Fclasses for children, and language
OL,15,Flessons for all. It comes as
OL,16,Forganisers say the number of people in
OL,17,FDumfries and Galloway with at least
OL,18,Fsome Gaelic ability has increased over
OL,19,Fthe past ten years.
