OL,7,F"I think Gaelic is part of Galloway.
OL,8,FIt's part of it's cultural heritage,"
OL,9,Fhe said. He pointed out that many
OL,10,Flocal place names, such as
OL,11,FKirkcudbright (Cille Chuithbeirt) and
OL,12,Fparticularly within Galloway (Gall-
OL,13,FGhaidhealaibh), have Gaelic origins,
OL,14,Freflecting the language's lasting
OL,15,Fpresence in the region.
OL,17,FDr Iain Howieson, who also sits on the
OL,18,FGaidhlig DumGal board, was also in
OL,19,Fattendance at the event in Thornhill.
OL,20,FHe suggested the language was on the
OL,21,Frise in Dumfries and Galloway.
