OL,7,F"In the recent census, it was found
OL,8,Fthat there were more than 2,000 people
OL,9,Fin the region who said that they had
OL,10,Fsome Gaelic. Now, that compares with
OL,11,Ffewer than a thousand in the 2011
OL,12,Fcensus. So it's definitely building."
OL,14,FAs part of World Gaelic Week, events
OL,15,Fhave been held in Newton Stewart,
OL,16,FAnnan, Dumfries, and Sanquhar, to name
OL,17,Fbut a few, as local organisations
OL,18,Fteamed up with Dumfries and Galloway
OL,19,FCouncil.
